defaultThe WLA is a partnership of six
default&#xa0;
defaultWest London councils - Barnet, Brent, Ealing, Harrow, 
defaultHillingdon and Hounslow.
default&#xa0;
defaultThese councils serve a population of 1.8 million people and have a joint annual expenditure of £3.8bn a year. There are over 77,000 VAT registered business and nearly 700,000 employees active in this West London area.
default&#xa0;
defaultThe WLA a
defaultims to: promote the interests of West London residents and businesses; improve and develop public services; and to reduce their costs through collaboration.
default&#xa0;
defaultIn addition to
default&#xa0;
defaultrepresenting the interests of West London in terms of economic development, transpor
defaultt and spatial planning policy, the WLA
default&#xa0;
defaultfacilitates a number of major improvement and efficiency programmes.
default&#xa0;
defaultThe WLA is also a founder member of the West London Partnership (WLP) which brings together the public, private and voluntary sectors in West Lond
defaulton to promote the economic, social and environmental interests of West London businesses and residents.
