default&#xa0;
defaultThe WLA also facilitates two Improvement and Efficiency Network events each year. These bring together council officers to discuss common issues and challenges and share best practice.
default&#xa0;
defaultIn addition to networking within West London, the WLA has been contributing to and learning from the experience of other councils in London
default and beyond
default. Since 2011 it has chaired the London Collaborative Efficiency Network (LCEN) and the London Economic De
defaultvelopment Sub-Regions Group.  The latter discusses key issues affecting 
defaultprocurement in 
defaultLondon such as
default;
default employment, funding opportunities and wider strategic economic development issues. 
default&#xa0;
defaultThe West London councils are represented on the London Procurement S
defaulttrategy Board by representatives from the Heads of Procurement and Treasurers Groups. They have been developing important linkages between the London-wide programme and the West London Procurement Board and Hub.  
