defaultWithin the WLA we operate a standardised 
defaultBenefit Realisationdefault 
defaultprocess. The concept is aimed at making the link between the cost savings and the benefits identified and established in a business case and secured from a procurement competition, to that which Finance Directors within a borough recognise as being delive
defaultred on the ground. Thus closing the budgeting
default /
default 
defaultprocurement 
defaultcycle loop where historically there has been little or no correlation between the costs and benefits that 
defaultare 
defaultclaim
defaulted as
default resultant from a procurement activity
default.
default&#xa0;
defaultWhilst this requires extra work as 
defaultit is a planned discipline within the procurement and finance departments of a borough 
default–
default it
default is useful in that it helps
default in bringing credibility and corporate ownership to the savings claims.
default&#xa0;
defaultThe Benefits Realisation process if overseen by a Board made up o
defaultf the Finance Directors from all of the boroughs, and is  chaired by an independent Treasurer from outside of the immediate WLA group.
